-- S.Korean stocks, won rise on eased geopolitical tensions 
-- By Joel Lee
-- Tue Aug 12, 2014 02:16AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, Aug 12 (Reuters) - South Korean shares and currency rose on Tuesday following easing geopolitical tensions that sparked rallies in the United States and Europe.

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> rose 0.10 percent at 2,041.47 points while the won <KRW=> ended onshore trade up 0.3 percent on the day at 1,026.4 per dollar. Foreign investors bought a net 94.9 billion won ($92.46 million) worth of KOSPI shares, buttressing on the main board.